column1: ## Stellar spectra for Roman Slitless Spectroscopy Data Challenge 2: Group 01
## Spectra generated from interpolating the grid of PHOENIX spectral
## library using pysynphot. The astrophysical parameters are taken randomly
## from the Gaia Data Release 3 golden sample of astrophysical parameters
## (Creevey et al. 2023). The tables are joined with the distance catalogue
## of Bailer-Jones et al. 2021. Only sources fainter than G = 17
## are taken

column1: ## gold_sample_oba_stars

## LOG_T   = 3.503431797 / log10 effective temperature in K
## LOG_L   = nan / log10 luminosity in solar luminosity
## R       = nan / stellar radius in solar radius
## MH      = -0.453500003 / metallicity
## DIST    = 162.471038818 / photogeometric distance in pc
## G_MAG   = 18.493772507 / G-band magnitude
## G_FLUX  = 7.541156715e+02 / G-band mean flux in counts/s
## A_0     = 1.008100033 / Monochromatic absorption A0
## flux_photlam is the PHOENIX luminosity normalized by the measured G-band
